    <item>
      <title>How to Write PureScript React Components to Replace JavaScript</title>
      <link>https://thomashoneyman.com/articles/replace-react-components-with-purescript/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 26 Jun 2019 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://thomashoneyman.com/articles/replace-react-components-with-purescript/</guid>
      <description>I have twice helped migrate large JavaScript apps to PureScript. At CitizenNet we replaced Angular with Halogen and at Awake Security we&amp;rsquo;ve replaced a React application with PureScript React. Both companies have experienced a dramatic drop in bugs and a commensurate rise in maintainability.
It&amp;rsquo;s relatively easy to replace React because PureScript has several React libraries (including support for Hooks and React Native). These libraries range from the low-level bindings of the react library to the higher-level react-basic and concur libraries (to name just a few).</description>
